                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d445">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">851.5151/950: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-09-08T20:00:00+01:00"
                            >September 8, 1936—8 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received September 8—1:55 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>843. From Cochran. Reference my 833, September 5, noon.<note n="17"
                        xml:id="d445fn17">Not printed.</note> French Minister of Finance handed to
                    me French text of document in question at 6 o’clock this evening. I am making
                    English translation which Rueff will check with me tonight. I may not therefore
                    cable text until Wednesday morning. Monick was at Ministry of Finance this
                    evening. He will leave for London tomorrow with text for British which cannot be
                    delivered before late Wednesday evening or Thursday morning. [Cochran.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
